Les Stroud was talking about how if you're traveling w/ horses and there's a thunderstorm the biggest danger is the horses getting scared by a lightning and going wild kicking you or running away out of fear. Reminds me of what the Hagakure says about disaster happening due...

... To superstitious peasants being afraid of a bad omen and summoning an actual disaster with their fear. Or how the immune system goes wild at an antigen and kills the entire organism in the reaction. Over-reacting is almost always worse than the things that make us over-react.
